        "content": "<p>we encountered some issues when using time zone in date query. how is FHIR treating time zones? is there a clear requirement for this?</p>",
        "id": 263866836,
        "sender_full_name": "Lital Inghel",
        "timestamp": 1638804665
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>It's discussed here: <a href=\"https://build.fhir.org/search.html#date\">https://build.fhir.org/search.html#date</a>.  Is there guidance you're looking for beyond that?</p>",
        "id": 263868160,
        "sender_full_name": "Lloyd McKenzie",
        "timestamp": 1638805167
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>it says<br>\n'Managing time zones and offsets and their impact on search is a very difficult area. The FHIR implementation community is still investigating and debating the best way to handle time zones. Implementation guides may make additional rules in this regard.'</p>\n<p>so are there any rules in regards to that?</p>",
